WEBVTT

00:01.392 --> 00:03.177
- Previously on
"God Friended Me"...

00:03.220 --> 00:04.308
God sent me
a friend request?

00:04.352 --> 00:05.657
Who's John Dove?

00:05.701 --> 00:06.963
- I think you just
saved my life.

00:07.007 --> 00:08.791
- Who the hell is Cara Bloom?

00:08.834 --> 00:10.184
- You wanna figure out
who's screwing with you.

00:10.227 --> 00:12.229
I'm a journalist.
I know how to find people.

00:12.273 --> 00:15.711
- Moved from Ohio to New York.
- She's Cara's mom.

00:15.754 --> 00:17.539
- Cara.
- Mom?

00:17.582 --> 00:19.062
- [crying]

00:19.106 --> 00:20.455
[horn honking, tires squealing]
- Cara!

00:20.498 --> 00:21.760
You stay with me, Cara.
- You're the guy

00:21.804 --> 00:23.110
from the subway.
- John Dove?

00:23.153 --> 00:24.894
She needs a doctor.
- I am a doctor.

00:24.937 --> 00:26.504
- I want to be
a part of your life.

00:26.548 --> 00:28.245
- I told you I'd help you
get to the bottom of it.

00:28.289 --> 00:30.160
Maybe we'll do some good
in the process.

00:30.204 --> 00:32.423
[cell phone buzzing]

00:32.467 --> 00:33.990
[cell phone chimes]

00:34.034 --> 00:35.992
[Banx & Ranx's "Answerphone"]

00:36.036 --> 00:37.341
- ♪ I've been talking to
your answerphone, na na ♪

00:37.385 --> 00:39.387
- New York City,

00:39.430 --> 00:42.955
a place where lives intersect
in the most surprising ways.

00:42.999 --> 00:45.088
Is it all part
of a grand design

00:45.132 --> 00:47.003
or a game of chance?

00:47.047 --> 00:51.399
A few days ago, someone calling
themselves God on Facebook

00:51.442 --> 00:53.488
started sending me random
friend suggestions

00:53.531 --> 00:55.055
from people I didn't know,

00:55.098 --> 00:56.752
like my new friend Cara.

00:56.795 --> 00:59.276
She's a journalist who
had writer's block.

00:59.320 --> 01:01.061
I helped her reconnect
with her mom,

01:01.104 --> 01:03.541
and now she's writing again.

01:03.585 --> 01:06.718
The thing is,
I know it's not God.

01:06.762 --> 01:08.894
I don't believe in God.

01:08.938 --> 01:12.507
But I am determined to figure
out who's behind this.

01:12.550 --> 01:14.900
Now, my best friend Rakesh
and I have been trying

01:14.944 --> 01:16.076
to track them down.

01:16.119 --> 01:17.686
[computer beeps]

01:17.729 --> 01:19.905
So far, they're winning.

01:19.949 --> 01:22.038
But it's not all bad.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.432
I did reconnect with my dad.

01:24.475 --> 01:26.695
Of course he's a reverend
and I'm an atheist,

01:26.738 --> 01:29.567
so we've got a long way to go,
but it's a start.

01:29.611 --> 01:32.048
And it makes
my sister Ali happy.

01:32.092 --> 01:34.877
She really wants us
to be a family again,

01:34.920 --> 01:37.097
and I'm pretty sure she's
using us as a case study

01:37.140 --> 01:38.750
for her graduate psych thesis.

01:38.794 --> 01:41.057
♪

01:41.101 --> 01:45.931
But for now I don't have time
to worry about the God account.

01:45.975 --> 01:47.411
And, sure, I'm intrigued,

01:47.455 --> 01:49.239
but I've got much bigger
things going on

01:49.283 --> 01:51.023
that demand my attention.

01:51.067 --> 01:53.591
A brand-new satellite radio
company is interested

01:53.635 --> 01:55.376
in my podcast,
"The Millennial Prophet."

01:55.419 --> 01:57.552
Now, I gotta keep
the details hush-hush,

01:57.595 --> 02:00.337
but here's hoping that next
time you hear from me,

02:00.381 --> 02:01.469
it's on a much
larger platform.

02:01.512 --> 02:03.471
[cell phone chimes and buzzes]

02:03.514 --> 02:05.777
- ♪ I've been talking to your
answerphone, na, na ♪

02:05.821 --> 02:08.780
- Nope.

02:08.824 --> 02:11.783
[mysterious music]

02:11.827 --> 02:16.962
♪

02:17.006 --> 02:18.834
- Let me get right to it,
Miles.

02:18.877 --> 02:21.358
When Frequency brought me over
from Sirius to launch a new

02:21.402 --> 02:24.187
satellite station,
I knew I had to have a podcast

02:24.231 --> 02:26.189
that would cut
through the noise.

02:26.233 --> 02:28.191
That podcast is yours.

02:28.235 --> 02:30.150
- [laughs]
Wow, thanks, man.

02:30.193 --> 02:32.195
- And "The Millennial Prophet"
is exactly the kind of show

02:32.239 --> 02:34.197
that we can grow
into an enormous hit.

02:34.241 --> 02:35.807
- Well, great.
Where do I sign?

02:35.851 --> 02:37.548
- I just--I just wanna
make sure that we're on

02:37.592 --> 02:40.856
the same page moving forward.
- Yeah, of--of course.

02:40.899 --> 02:43.075
- Now, the last few podcasts,
you mentioned something

02:43.119 --> 02:45.382
called the God account.

02:45.426 --> 02:48.472
That--is that supposed to be
some kind of metaphor, or--

02:48.516 --> 02:51.301
- Uh, yeah.

02:51.345 --> 02:52.607
Yeah.

02:52.650 --> 02:54.261
- Clever.

02:54.304 --> 02:55.871
Drop it.

02:55.914 --> 02:57.655
- Oh.
- Yeah, it's off-message.

02:57.699 --> 03:02.573
See, I want the guy beating
the drum of a godless world.

03:02.617 --> 03:05.141
I don't want you to meet
your audience in the middle.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.535
I want you to pick a lane.
Stick to it.

03:07.578 --> 03:09.450
So no more God account talk,
okay?

03:11.278 --> 03:12.235
What do you say, Miles?

03:14.542 --> 03:15.978
- You know what?
I say I'm your man.

03:16.021 --> 03:17.545
[both laughing]
- Congrats, Miles.

03:17.588 --> 03:18.676
- Thank you.
[cell phone chimes and buzzes]

03:18.720 --> 03:19.677
- Come on,
I'll show you around.

03:19.721 --> 03:21.070
[cell phone chimes]

03:22.941 --> 03:25.509
[mysterious music]

03:25.553 --> 03:27.990
Ready, Miles?

03:28.033 --> 03:29.339
- Sorry.

03:29.383 --> 03:32.037
[thunder rumbles]

03:32.081 --> 03:34.562
[rain pattering]

03:34.605 --> 03:36.651
♪

03:36.694 --> 03:39.044
- Look at that.
It's raining.

03:39.088 --> 03:44.920
♪

03:44.963 --> 03:46.704
[thunder rumbles]

03:46.748 --> 03:48.706
- You wanna see me take a call?

03:48.750 --> 03:50.186
Pretty incredible in action.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.144
- Not really.

03:52.188 --> 03:53.711
But you are pretty cute
in that headset.

03:53.755 --> 03:55.278
- Does that mean you
wanna go out again?

03:55.322 --> 03:56.845
- Sure.
- Great.

03:56.888 --> 03:58.673
I'll make reservations
for lunch tomorrow.

03:58.716 --> 04:02.067
Two, actually, in case, uh,
you prefer the vegan option.

04:02.111 --> 04:04.722
- Tomorrow I have--
I have plans.

04:04.766 --> 04:06.115
You know what?
We'll figure it out later.

04:06.158 --> 04:07.377
- Okay.
- I gotta go.

04:07.421 --> 04:09.423
- B--bye.
[cell phone beeps]

04:09.466 --> 04:13.731
She has...plans.
Everybody has plans.

04:13.775 --> 04:16.560
Plans aren't a big deal.

04:16.604 --> 04:19.389
[cell phone keyboard clicking]

04:19.433 --> 04:21.783
So?
Did you get the gig?

04:21.826 --> 04:23.611
- I got it!
- Ah!

04:23.654 --> 04:24.612
Holy...

04:24.655 --> 04:25.961
Dude, that's incredible.

04:26.004 --> 04:27.136
- Heading back down there

04:27.179 --> 04:28.790
tomorrow to record some promos,

04:28.833 --> 04:29.965
meet the engineer, producers,

04:30.008 --> 04:31.096
my whole team.

04:31.140 --> 04:32.402
- You got a team?
- Yeah.

04:32.446 --> 04:34.056
Best part?
I put my two weeks in.

04:34.099 --> 04:36.319
I'm finally getting
out of this place.

04:36.363 --> 04:37.842
[chuckles]

04:37.886 --> 04:40.149
- Miles, you're the most
successful person I know.

04:42.194 --> 04:43.413
What?

04:43.457 --> 04:44.588
- Check this out.

04:44.632 --> 04:48.592
[mysterious music]

04:48.636 --> 04:49.811
Whoever's behind the God
account

04:49.854 --> 04:50.986
changed their profile pic

04:51.029 --> 04:52.335
right after
I accepted the gig.

04:52.379 --> 04:53.815
- Ominous.
- No, no, no, no.

04:53.858 --> 04:55.338
Literally, it's no joke.

04:55.382 --> 04:56.992
I said yes,
got the notification,

04:57.035 --> 04:58.341
and it started to rain.

04:58.385 --> 04:59.821
- Miles, there was rain
in the forecast.

04:59.864 --> 05:01.301
I brought an umbrella to work.

05:01.344 --> 05:02.519
Besides, they probably hacked

05:02.563 --> 05:03.999
your phone.
For all you know,

05:04.042 --> 05:05.566
they were listening in.

05:05.609 --> 05:08.656
- No, the point is
they fired a warning shot.

05:08.699 --> 05:10.527
- Okay, so what?

05:10.571 --> 05:12.573
You really think the people
behind this account don't want

05:12.616 --> 05:14.836
you to work at Frequency?
- Consider the facts.

05:14.879 --> 05:16.403
They erased my
presentation last week,

05:16.446 --> 05:17.882
almost cost me the interview--

05:17.926 --> 05:19.580
I can't have them
screwing this up for me.

05:19.623 --> 05:20.842
We gotta find them.

05:20.885 --> 05:26.282
♪

05:26.326 --> 05:28.371
- Wait, I think
I just figured out how.

05:28.415 --> 05:31.156
They changed their profile pic.
- Yeah, I'm aware.

05:31.200 --> 05:32.549
- Yes, but are you aware that

05:32.593 --> 05:33.768
every picture uploaded online

05:33.811 --> 05:35.160
is geotagged?

05:35.204 --> 05:36.684
All we have to do
is run an image search.

05:36.727 --> 05:38.686
Once we get a match,
I can trace the exact location

05:38.729 --> 05:40.775
it was uploaded from.
It's just it'll take some time.

05:40.818 --> 05:42.864
- Great.
- Yeah.

05:42.907 --> 05:45.083
- So what do I do
in the meantime?

05:45.127 --> 05:47.259
- You got a friend suggestion.
Play along.

05:47.303 --> 05:48.522
See where it goes.

05:49.740 --> 05:52.700
- Fine.
Katie Brooks.

05:52.743 --> 05:55.659
Says she's a waitress
at the Blue Pin Café.

05:55.703 --> 05:58.009
I'll call Cara and have her
meet me there for dinner.

05:58.053 --> 05:59.663
♪

05:59.707 --> 06:01.709
- Cara?

06:01.752 --> 06:03.493
- What?
What?

06:03.537 --> 06:05.147
What? She said she
wanted to be looped in.

06:05.190 --> 06:07.367
- Mm-hmm, to dinner.
I understand.

06:07.410 --> 06:08.977
- Bro, it is not
even like that.

06:09.020 --> 06:10.718
We're just friends.
- [laughs]

06:10.761 --> 06:12.502
Miles, "just friends"
is the beginning

06:12.546 --> 06:16.419
of every great romantic
comedy ever, so...

06:16.463 --> 06:18.639
♪

06:18.682 --> 06:20.292
- Yeah, I'm glad you called.

06:20.336 --> 06:21.859
Uh, when did you get
the new friend suggestion?

06:21.903 --> 06:24.949
- A few days ago.
- Well, why didn't you tell me?

06:24.993 --> 06:27.038
- Well, because with everything
going on with my podcast,

06:27.082 --> 06:29.998
I was hoping to focus on that
and this would go away.

06:30.041 --> 06:31.608
- You know, Miles, I think
you're looking at this whole

06:31.652 --> 06:33.175
God account thing wrong.

06:33.218 --> 06:34.829
I mean, why don't you stop
seeing it as a nuisance

06:34.872 --> 06:36.047
and see it for what it is?

06:36.091 --> 06:38.354
- Which is what,
ice cream lady?

06:40.225 --> 06:43.011
- Which is, if we find out
who's behind this account,

06:43.054 --> 06:44.491
that'll make
for an amazing story.

06:44.534 --> 06:46.841
And if it turns out to be God,

06:46.884 --> 06:48.364
greatest mystery
of the universe solved.

06:48.408 --> 06:51.236
Win-win.
- Can I ask you something?

06:51.280 --> 06:54.239
- Yeah, sure.
- [laughs]

06:54.283 --> 06:56.720
Do you always eat
ice cream for dinner?

06:58.592 --> 06:59.984
- Only when I'm stressed.
- Mm.

07:00.028 --> 07:01.638
- So don't judge.
- No judgment.

07:01.682 --> 07:02.944
No judgment.

07:02.987 --> 07:06.469
I actually think
it's pretty adorable.

07:06.513 --> 07:09.472
- Oh.
Okay, then.

07:09.516 --> 07:11.996
- So, you wanna talk about it?

07:13.563 --> 07:16.218
- What?
- You said you're stressed.

07:16.261 --> 07:17.437
- Oh.
- I mean, it's cool

07:17.480 --> 07:18.481
if you don't wanna
talk about it.

07:18.525 --> 07:21.484
- No, no, it's fine.
Um...

07:21.528 --> 07:24.748
it's just my mom.

07:24.792 --> 07:28.230
I spent my whole life
trying to find her.

07:28.273 --> 07:31.625
And now that I have,
it's like...

07:31.668 --> 07:33.757
I don't know how
to take the next step.

07:33.801 --> 07:35.498
- Yeah, I told my dad
about the Frequency gig.

07:35.542 --> 07:37.108
- Mm-hmm.
- That was a quick convo.

07:37.152 --> 07:38.762
I mean, I don't know
what I was expecting.

07:38.806 --> 07:40.808
It's not like he ever listened
to the podcast anyways.

07:40.851 --> 07:43.332
- [sighs]
It's tough.

07:43.375 --> 07:45.508
I mean, I saw my mom
at my sister's soccer game.

07:45.552 --> 07:47.510
- Oh.
- It was so awkward.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.381
And we're supposed to see
each other again tomorrow,

07:49.425 --> 07:51.514
and I don't even know what
we're gonna talk about.

07:53.385 --> 07:55.779
It's just a lot harder
than I thought it would be.

07:55.823 --> 07:57.215
- Yeah.

07:57.259 --> 07:59.566
[doorbell jingles]

07:59.609 --> 08:02.046
- Oh, hey, hey.
[cell phone chimes]

08:02.090 --> 08:03.961
Look.
It's her.

08:04.005 --> 08:05.615
♪

08:05.659 --> 08:07.574
- What are you gonna say?

08:07.617 --> 08:09.532
- I dunno.
Do you have any ideas?

08:09.576 --> 08:11.752
- Just don't tell
her God sent you.

08:11.795 --> 08:13.188
- You're late again.

08:13.231 --> 08:15.320
- I know, I know.
I'm sorry.

08:15.364 --> 08:18.454
- What's the excuse this time?
- Look, I'm here now, right?

08:18.498 --> 08:19.760
- Well, hey, don't
walk away from me.

08:19.803 --> 08:21.413
- Whoa.
- I said I'm sorry.

08:21.457 --> 08:23.285
I had to get Nate home.

08:23.328 --> 08:25.330
- You know, I'm sick and tired
of the damn excuses, Katie.

08:25.374 --> 08:26.723
- Hey, hey, hey, hey,
take--take it easy.

08:26.767 --> 08:28.246
- Excuse me?
- You're causing a scene.

08:28.290 --> 08:29.770
And that is no way
to talk to a lady.

08:29.813 --> 08:32.294
- Thank you, but, uh,
it's really not necessary.

08:32.337 --> 08:34.339
- Yeah, uh, Romeo,
why don't you take a seat

08:34.383 --> 08:35.471
and mind your own
damn business?

08:35.515 --> 08:36.994
- [laughs]
Romeo?

08:37.038 --> 08:38.866
- In this situation,
he's really more of a Mercutio.

08:38.909 --> 08:41.303
- Listen, I really think
you owe her an apology.

08:41.346 --> 08:42.565
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

08:42.609 --> 08:44.175
- I said it's fine.
- No.

08:44.219 --> 08:45.263
Katie, he's right.

08:46.264 --> 08:47.657
I'm sorry.

08:47.701 --> 08:49.354
You're fired!

08:49.398 --> 08:50.834
- Whoa, wait, no, no.
That is not what I meant.

08:50.878 --> 08:52.662
- Wait, wait, wait.
Please.

08:52.706 --> 08:54.490
- And you, pal, can get
the hell out of my restaurant.

08:54.534 --> 08:55.535
- You can't do this!

08:55.578 --> 08:58.538
[tense music]

08:58.581 --> 08:59.930
♪

08:59.974 --> 09:01.932
Thanks...

09:01.976 --> 09:03.238
for nothing.

09:03.281 --> 09:06.894
♪

09:06.937 --> 09:09.026
- All right,
we're off to a great start.

09:09.070 --> 09:10.550
♪

09:10.593 --> 09:12.290
[doorbell jingles]

09:22.953 --> 09:24.607
- Wait, you're serious?
You got her fired?

09:24.651 --> 09:28.089
Miles, you gotta be
the worst do-gooder ever.

09:28.132 --> 09:30.657
- Not helpful, Rakesh.
- You did the right thing.

09:30.700 --> 09:32.615
How could you have known
that she was gonna get fired?

09:32.659 --> 09:35.444
- Well, I should have
never stepped in.

09:35.487 --> 09:38.795
- Hey, Cara,
can I ask you a, um,

09:38.839 --> 09:40.797
non-God-account-related
question?

09:40.841 --> 09:42.320
- Sure.

09:42.364 --> 09:45.280
- So, like, if a guy you
like asks you to lunch,

09:45.323 --> 09:48.675
why would you say
you have other plans?

09:48.718 --> 09:50.459
- Because I had other plans?

09:50.502 --> 09:52.113
- Now that we
solved that mystery,

09:52.156 --> 09:54.115
can you get me Katie's address?

09:54.158 --> 09:55.638
- Uh, sure.
Why?

09:55.682 --> 09:58.293
- Because I wanna go
down and apologize.

09:58.336 --> 10:00.512
I mean, I feel really bad,
and...

10:00.556 --> 10:02.384
I don't know, maybe I can
help her get a new job.

10:02.427 --> 10:04.473
- What are you,
careerbuilder.com?

10:04.516 --> 10:06.127
- Yeah, he has a point.

10:06.170 --> 10:08.651
Who do you know that
could get her a job?

10:08.695 --> 10:10.261
- There is one person.

10:10.305 --> 10:12.742
- Miles, I can't hire her.
- Why not?

10:12.786 --> 10:14.483
Aren't you, like, the manager?

10:14.526 --> 10:16.485
I mean, you must have the
authority to hire bartenders.

10:16.528 --> 10:19.053
- I do.
But you said she's a waitress.

10:19.096 --> 10:21.316
We're looking for
experienced bartenders.

10:21.359 --> 10:23.492
Like someone who can make
a Long Island, for example.

10:23.535 --> 10:26.800
- Oh, gin, white rum, tequila,
vodka, splash of sour,

10:26.843 --> 10:29.063
and a splash of Coke.

10:29.106 --> 10:31.152
Oh, I used to date a bartender.

10:31.195 --> 10:33.850
- Oh, oh, speaking of drinks,
I invited some friends

10:33.894 --> 10:35.504
to the bar later
to celebrate your good news.

10:35.547 --> 10:36.984
- You did?
- Of course, Miles.

10:37.027 --> 10:38.986
This is a big deal.

10:39.029 --> 10:41.553
[snaps fingers]
Cara, you should come.

10:43.381 --> 10:46.123
- Uh, sure.
Yeah, uh, I'll be there.

10:48.256 --> 10:49.605
- Good.

10:51.041 --> 10:53.740
[cell phone chimes and buzzes]

10:53.783 --> 10:55.698
- Hey, Rakesh just sent
me Katie's address.

10:55.742 --> 10:57.265
Okay, I'm gonna go down
there and apologize.

10:57.308 --> 10:58.832
- Cool, yeah.
I'll go with you.

10:58.875 --> 11:00.442
- I thought you were
meeting up with your mom.

11:00.485 --> 11:02.705
- Yeah, I can just reschedule.

11:02.749 --> 11:04.446
But I shouldn't, should I?

11:04.489 --> 11:06.883
Okay, I'll see you later.
- Okay.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.668
- Hey, Miles.

11:08.711 --> 11:12.106
I was thinking maybe you
could invite Dad tonight.

11:12.149 --> 11:13.890
- [sighs Yeah,
I don't think this is

11:13.934 --> 11:15.587
the kind of thing Dad
would celebrate.

11:15.631 --> 11:18.068
I mean, he's never even
listened to my podcast.

11:18.112 --> 11:20.331
- Maybe he'll change his mind.

11:20.375 --> 11:22.203
- Have you ever known
Reverend Finder

11:22.246 --> 11:23.595
to change his mind?

11:26.163 --> 11:33.170
♪

11:36.434 --> 11:38.436
- Ali!
- Dad.

11:38.480 --> 11:41.744
- [laughs]
This is a nice surprise.

11:41.788 --> 11:43.615
- Oh, you got a second?
- Of course.

11:43.659 --> 11:46.401
- Okay, well...

11:46.444 --> 11:48.229
I know it's short notice...
- Mm-hmm.

11:48.272 --> 11:50.927
- But I am throwing a little
get-together at the bar tonight

11:50.971 --> 11:54.322
for Miles's podcast,
and I want you to be there.

11:54.365 --> 11:56.585
- And you came all the way
down here to ask me that?

11:56.628 --> 11:59.762
- No, I came all the way down
here to convince you to come.

11:59.806 --> 12:01.068
- Mm.

12:01.111 --> 12:02.765
- Look, Dad, I know you hoped

12:02.809 --> 12:04.593
his podcast would go away,

12:04.636 --> 12:06.551
but it's not a hobby anymore.

12:06.595 --> 12:09.076
This is his career.

12:09.119 --> 12:10.817
You can't ignore that.
- I'm not ignoring it.

12:10.860 --> 12:11.992
- But you've never
listened to it.

12:12.035 --> 12:12.993
- Ali--
- Dad.

12:13.036 --> 12:14.255
- Mm-mm, mm-mm.

12:14.298 --> 12:15.778
- Look, as a Reverend,

12:15.822 --> 12:18.607
I don't expect you
to support his views.

12:18.650 --> 12:22.437
But as his father, I do
expect you to support him.

12:22.480 --> 12:25.483
Or things between the two
of you will never get better.

12:30.837 --> 12:34.666
- You are going to be an
excellent therapist someday.

12:34.710 --> 12:35.885
- Someday?
- Mm-hmm.

12:35.929 --> 12:36.930
- [harrumphs]

12:36.973 --> 12:39.236
[both laughing]

12:39.280 --> 12:40.934
- Well, that's why we're here,
Mr. Davis.

12:40.977 --> 12:43.675
In reclaiming your identity,
time is of the essence.

12:43.719 --> 12:45.199
[computer beeps]

12:45.242 --> 12:47.288
Actually, sorry, I'm gonna
have to call you back.

12:47.331 --> 12:50.944
[intriguing music]

12:50.987 --> 12:52.467
God's in Hell's Kitchen.

12:52.510 --> 12:54.295
♪

12:54.338 --> 12:55.862
That sick genius.

12:55.905 --> 13:00.562
♪

13:00.605 --> 13:03.608
[police siren
blaring distantly]

13:13.009 --> 13:16.317
[cell phone buzzes and chimes]

13:16.360 --> 13:19.146
[cell phone chimes]

13:19.189 --> 13:21.148
- Yeah?
- Hi.

13:21.191 --> 13:22.540
I'm Miles.

13:23.933 --> 13:27.154
I'm the guy that got
you fired yesterday.

13:27.197 --> 13:29.025
- What the hell
are you doing here?

13:29.069 --> 13:31.985
- Um...
- How did you get my address?

13:32.028 --> 13:33.769
- I had a friend
look it up online.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.510
- Okay, good-bye.
- Wait, wait, wait, look, look.

13:35.553 --> 13:38.121
I--I just wanted to come
by to apologize, okay?

13:38.165 --> 13:39.775
I--I felt really bad
about what happened,

13:39.819 --> 13:42.909
so I looked up some
waitressing jobs online.

13:42.952 --> 13:45.346
Now, I have them here
or I can email them to you.

13:45.389 --> 13:46.913
Look, there's one midtown.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.045
That may be too far,
but if you take the C train,

13:49.089 --> 13:51.178
you can be there in 30 minutes.

13:51.221 --> 13:53.049
- You're serious?
- Yes.

13:55.486 --> 13:59.360
- Look, uh, you seem genuine--

13:59.403 --> 14:01.057
weird but genuine.

14:01.101 --> 14:02.885
So, the--
the gesture's appreciated.

14:02.929 --> 14:04.626
But, uh, it's fine.

14:04.669 --> 14:06.889
My boss and I had been having
those kind of arguments

14:06.933 --> 14:10.675
for months now, so it was bound
to end sooner or later.

14:10.719 --> 14:13.461
I'm actually on my way to,
uh, an interview now, so...

14:13.504 --> 14:15.376
- Oh, that's good.
Great.

14:15.419 --> 14:18.945
Well, look, if there's
anything else I can do...

14:18.988 --> 14:21.556
- No, but I appreciate
the offer.

14:21.599 --> 14:23.079
[video game beeping]

14:23.123 --> 14:24.994
- [brightly] Hey!

14:25.038 --> 14:26.778
What's up, little man?
[chuckles]

14:26.822 --> 14:29.085
Nice hat.

14:29.129 --> 14:31.914
- Nate, baby, why don't you go
back in the other room?

14:31.958 --> 14:34.395
[cell phone rings]

14:34.438 --> 14:37.572
I gotta take this.
Um, thank you.

14:37.615 --> 14:39.704
- Yes.
- For coming by, so...

14:39.748 --> 14:42.359
[laughs]

14:42.403 --> 14:44.492
Hey, where are you?

14:44.535 --> 14:47.190
That's halfway across town.
Jen, I'm already late.

14:47.234 --> 14:49.062
I need this job.

14:49.105 --> 14:51.238
Okay, can you just meet me
at the restaurant and then just

14:51.281 --> 14:53.066
sit with Nate while--
while I do the interview?

14:53.109 --> 14:54.371
[disheartened music]

14:54.415 --> 14:55.416
No, I understand.

14:55.459 --> 14:58.245
♪

14:58.288 --> 15:00.769
Oh, baby.

15:00.812 --> 15:03.946
The universe really
hates your momma.

15:03.990 --> 15:06.644
[sighs]
What am I gonna do?

15:08.516 --> 15:10.953
[intriguing music]

15:10.997 --> 15:15.479
♪

15:15.523 --> 15:19.005
Hey!
Mr. Good Samaritan.

15:19.048 --> 15:20.484
You still wanna help?

15:30.016 --> 15:32.975
[Rita Ora's "Your Song"]

15:33.019 --> 15:35.804
[mellow electronic pop music]

15:35.847 --> 15:37.719
- So, what's your deal, Miles?

15:37.762 --> 15:39.590
Are you, uh, with
a church or something?

15:39.634 --> 15:41.114
- [laughs]
What?

15:41.157 --> 15:44.291
No, no.
Why?

15:44.334 --> 15:48.034
- I don't know.
You seem abnormally charitable,

15:48.077 --> 15:52.212
like one of those
people doing God's work.

15:52.255 --> 15:55.911
- No, that would be my father.
He's a reverend.

15:55.955 --> 15:57.260
- Aha.

15:57.304 --> 15:59.654
Well, clearly it rubbed off.

15:59.697 --> 16:02.700
[cell phone buzzing]

16:03.963 --> 16:05.529
You need to get that?

16:07.705 --> 16:09.359
- No, no.

16:09.403 --> 16:11.100
So, is it just you and Nate?

16:11.144 --> 16:13.494
- Yep, ever since his dad went
off to Europe to, uh,

16:13.537 --> 16:15.191
tour with his band.

16:15.235 --> 16:16.932
- How long ago was that?

16:16.976 --> 16:18.586
- Six years.

16:18.629 --> 16:20.892
Right after Nate was
diagnosed with autism.

16:20.936 --> 16:22.982
- That must've been tough.

16:23.025 --> 16:26.333
- It's been the two
of us ever since.

16:26.376 --> 16:27.682
But we get by.

16:30.163 --> 16:31.816
All right, buddy.

16:31.860 --> 16:34.123
Momma has a meeting, so, um,

16:34.167 --> 16:36.734
Miles here is gonna
hang out with you, okay?

16:36.778 --> 16:39.128
And then after, we can, uh--
we can grab some ice cream.

16:39.172 --> 16:40.564
You'd like that, right?

16:42.740 --> 16:44.177
I know.

16:44.220 --> 16:45.874
Momma's trying to bribe you
with some ice cream

16:45.917 --> 16:47.049
because she's so desperate,

16:47.093 --> 16:50.618
she's leaving you
with a stranger.

16:50.661 --> 16:52.707
But I think he's okay,
don't you?

16:57.842 --> 17:01.585
Okay, um...here you go.

17:06.851 --> 17:10.203
Look, uh,
here's the thing about Nate.

17:10.246 --> 17:12.553
Um, he's nonverbal.
- Mm.

17:12.596 --> 17:13.989
- So he's not
gonna talk to you.

17:14.033 --> 17:15.338
At all.
- Okay.

17:15.382 --> 17:18.254
- And he doesn't like
to be touched

17:18.298 --> 17:21.692
or doesn't make eye contact.
- Strong and silent type.

17:21.736 --> 17:23.955
- I got you.
- [chuckles, sighs]

17:23.999 --> 17:25.696
All you really need to do
is just sit here

17:25.740 --> 17:28.351
and keep him company
until I'm done.

17:28.395 --> 17:30.353
- Don't worry, okay?

17:30.397 --> 17:33.487
I'm not gonna let
anything happen to him.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.793
- Good.

17:35.837 --> 17:39.667
But just to be sure, let me
see your driver's license.

17:39.710 --> 17:41.712
- Oh, okay.

17:41.756 --> 17:43.671
There you go.

17:43.714 --> 17:46.587
- Yeah, I'm gonna
hold on to this.

17:46.630 --> 17:48.458
I know where you live now.

17:48.502 --> 17:54.508
♪

17:57.859 --> 18:00.470
- So, have you seen
your friend Miles lately?

18:00.514 --> 18:01.906
- Uh, yeah.

18:01.950 --> 18:03.343
Yeah, I was with him earlier,
actually.

18:03.386 --> 18:07.042
- He's a nice guy.
- Is he cute?

18:07.086 --> 18:08.435
[both laugh]

18:08.478 --> 18:10.132
- Uh, what?

18:10.176 --> 18:13.048
- It's a simple question.

18:13.092 --> 18:15.050
- You're 12, right?

18:15.094 --> 18:18.053
- Well, yeah,
but I'm a New York 12,

18:18.097 --> 18:19.881
which--I'm practically 16.

18:19.924 --> 18:21.361
- Excuse me, you are not.

18:21.404 --> 18:23.232
- I know, Mom.
- [laughs]

18:23.276 --> 18:25.060
- I'll be back here in an hour.
Bye, Cara.

18:25.104 --> 18:26.888
- Bye.
- Bye, Liv.

18:30.239 --> 18:33.416
She's great.
- She's growing up so fast.

18:39.944 --> 18:42.164
You still run?

18:42.208 --> 18:44.384
- Uh, yeah.
Yeah, every morning.

18:44.427 --> 18:45.472
- Me too.

18:48.562 --> 18:50.607
So, how's work?

18:50.651 --> 18:52.479
- Uh, it's good.

18:52.522 --> 18:54.481
- Oh, great.
[both chuckle uncomfortably]

18:54.524 --> 18:56.744
I read your articles.

18:56.787 --> 18:59.312
- Which ones?
- All of them.

18:59.355 --> 19:02.576
You're a great writer.

19:02.619 --> 19:06.319
So were you a journalism
major in college?

19:06.362 --> 19:09.235
- Uh, yeah.
Yeah, I was.

19:11.628 --> 19:13.587
[stirring music]

19:13.630 --> 19:16.938
- I'm trying, Cara.

19:16.981 --> 19:19.680
♪

19:19.723 --> 19:22.857
- [sighs] I know.
It's just, um...

19:22.900 --> 19:26.600
You keep asking me all these
questions about my life.

19:26.643 --> 19:28.732
Kind of a reminder
that you weren't in it.

19:28.776 --> 19:35.739
♪

19:35.783 --> 19:38.394
I'm--I'm sorry.
- No. [sniffles]

19:38.438 --> 19:39.526
It's okay.

19:39.569 --> 19:42.572
[cell phone ringing]

19:45.140 --> 19:46.881
- Oh, you know what?
It's, uh--it's work.

19:46.924 --> 19:50.624
I--I gotta take it.

19:50.667 --> 19:52.103
[sighs]

19:52.147 --> 19:53.453
Rakesh, impeccable timing.
What's up?

19:53.496 --> 19:54.932
- Finally someone
picks up the phone.

19:54.976 --> 19:56.630
Listen, I got a lock
on God's location.

19:56.673 --> 19:57.979
He's in Hell's Kitchen
right now.

19:58.022 --> 19:59.546
- Okay, just text
me the address.

19:59.589 --> 20:01.112
I'll meet you there.
- I will, I will.

20:01.156 --> 20:02.375
But I need you to go get Miles,
all right?

20:02.418 --> 20:03.767
He's not picking up my call.

20:03.811 --> 20:07.118
He is at Dom's Diner
on the East Side.

20:07.162 --> 20:08.816
- How do you know that?

20:08.859 --> 20:10.861
- I just tracked his location
on Find My Friends.

20:10.905 --> 20:12.472
Doesn't everyone do that?

20:12.515 --> 20:14.430
- No.

20:14.474 --> 20:15.953
But, uh, I'll go get him.

20:18.347 --> 20:20.175
Um, I'm so sorry.

20:20.219 --> 20:21.959
I'm following a story,
so I have to go.

20:22.003 --> 20:24.527
- Oh, it's okay.
I understand.

20:24.571 --> 20:26.181
Bye.

20:26.225 --> 20:28.966
♪

20:29.010 --> 20:31.317
[mysterious music]

20:31.360 --> 20:36.278
[cell phone beeping]
- [humming]

20:36.322 --> 20:42.806
[beeping continues]

20:46.332 --> 20:47.637
- Jaya.

20:47.681 --> 20:50.466
♪

20:50.510 --> 20:51.946
[rapid beeping]

20:51.989 --> 20:56.124
♪

20:56.167 --> 20:59.736
- Hey, you know what?
I'm a Yankees fan too, Nate.

20:59.780 --> 21:02.086
Who's your favorite player?
Ooh, let me guess.

21:02.130 --> 21:05.089
Aaron Judge.
[laughs]

21:07.091 --> 21:10.094
[cell phone buzzes]

21:15.361 --> 21:17.711
Hey, Eric.

21:17.754 --> 21:19.582
Yeah, good, man.

21:19.626 --> 21:26.372
♪

21:26.415 --> 21:28.417
Oh, no, no, no,
we're absolutely still on

21:28.461 --> 21:30.463
for this afternoon, mm-hmm.
Wait, Nate.

21:30.506 --> 21:31.942
Hey.

21:31.986 --> 21:35.119
Um, no, yes.
I will see you in an hour.

21:35.163 --> 21:36.773
Nate.

21:36.817 --> 21:39.428
Nate, Nate, buddy.
Hey, hey, where are you going?

21:39.472 --> 21:41.778
Nate, we've gotta get back
to the restaurant.

21:41.822 --> 21:43.345
Okay, good, you stopped.

21:43.389 --> 21:44.955
Now, can we please go
back into the diner?

21:44.999 --> 21:47.044
♪

21:47.088 --> 21:48.263
Okay, or we can go in here.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.178
Nate, Nate!

21:50.221 --> 21:52.702
Nate, hey, your mom's gonna be
out of her meeting really soon

21:52.746 --> 21:54.574
and we gotta get back in
the booth when she's done.

21:54.617 --> 21:57.185
Nate.
[groans quietly]

21:57.228 --> 21:58.926
♪

21:58.969 --> 22:01.755
Okay, you like the pianos.
Um...

22:04.235 --> 22:06.194
You know what?
I'll tell you this.

22:06.237 --> 22:10.416
I'll play you one quick song,
and then we have to go back.

22:10.459 --> 22:11.982
Okay?

22:14.376 --> 22:15.725
Okay?

22:15.769 --> 22:18.511
Okay, wow.
Yes, um...

22:18.554 --> 22:22.123
okay, it's very simple.
Uh, all major notes.

22:22.166 --> 22:28.434
E, G, B, D, F--
"every good boy does fine."

22:28.477 --> 22:32.394
My mom was in charge
of my dad's church choir.

22:32.438 --> 22:33.961
She taught me how to play.

22:34.004 --> 22:36.485
It's really simple
once you get the hang of it.

22:36.529 --> 22:38.444
[chuckles]

22:38.487 --> 22:40.359
This was one of her favorites.

22:44.232 --> 22:49.977
♪ Sometimes in our lives

22:50.020 --> 22:53.284
♪ We all have pain

22:53.328 --> 22:58.202
♪ We all have sorrow

22:58.246 --> 22:59.987
♪ But

23:00.030 --> 23:02.990
♪ If we are wise

23:03.033 --> 23:05.993
♪ We know that there's

23:06.036 --> 23:09.649
♪ Hope for tomorrow

23:09.692 --> 23:12.652
[pop music playing]

23:12.695 --> 23:19.702
♪

23:21.487 --> 23:23.184
- Hey.

23:23.227 --> 23:26.056
Wait, you're that girl that was
with Miles yesterday, right?

23:26.100 --> 23:28.145
- Uh, yeah.
Yeah, it's Cara.

23:28.189 --> 23:29.712
Um, I came here
looking for him.

23:29.756 --> 23:31.061
Have you seen him?

23:31.105 --> 23:32.715
- Yeah, he's watching my son.

23:35.544 --> 23:37.677
Nate?

23:37.720 --> 23:39.287
Nate?

23:39.330 --> 23:41.681
[Bill Withers' "Lean on Me"
playing on piano]

23:41.724 --> 23:44.335
♪

23:44.379 --> 23:49.689
- ♪ Lean on me
when you're not strong ♪

23:49.732 --> 23:52.605
♪ And I'll be your friend

23:52.648 --> 23:57.044
♪ And I'll help you carry on
- [exhales]

23:57.087 --> 23:58.393
- ♪ For

23:58.437 --> 24:00.917
♪ It won't be long

24:00.961 --> 24:03.703
♪ Till I'm gonna need

24:03.746 --> 24:08.229
♪ Somebody to lean on

24:08.272 --> 24:11.232
[stirring music]

24:11.275 --> 24:12.929
♪

24:12.973 --> 24:14.061
[chuckles]

24:14.104 --> 24:17.630
♪

24:17.673 --> 24:20.459
- [chuckles breathlessly]

24:20.502 --> 24:26.465
♪

24:28.118 --> 24:29.250
- Nate, let's go.
Now.

24:29.293 --> 24:30.817
- Katie?
- All you had to do

24:30.860 --> 24:32.645
was sit there, and you leave?

24:32.688 --> 24:34.560
I thought I could trust you.
- Well, we were coming back.

24:34.603 --> 24:38.085
- Stay away from me and my son.
Come on.

24:38.128 --> 24:40.435
- Wait, K--Katie.
Wait, listen.

24:40.479 --> 24:43.220
Katie, listen to me, please.
I'm sorry.

24:43.264 --> 24:44.744
Katie, I'm sorry!

24:44.787 --> 24:48.965
♪

24:49.009 --> 24:51.794
- Miles, what is going on?

24:51.838 --> 24:53.013
- I was just trying to help.

24:53.056 --> 24:54.493
♪

24:54.536 --> 24:55.798
- Wait, what--what
are you doing here?

24:55.842 --> 24:57.496
I thought you were
with your mom.

24:57.539 --> 24:59.149
- Yeah, I was, but Rakesh got
a lead on the God account.

24:59.193 --> 25:00.847
I came to get you.

25:00.890 --> 25:02.675
- Well, I'm sorry you
came all down this way,

25:02.718 --> 25:04.938
but I have an important
meeting I have to get to, so...

25:04.981 --> 25:06.722
- Wait, so you're
just gonna walk away?

25:06.766 --> 25:09.290
- Look, I tried to help, okay?

25:09.333 --> 25:11.422
And I didn't do anything
but make things worse.

25:11.466 --> 25:12.598
She's better off without me.
- No.

25:12.641 --> 25:14.382
No, don't do that.

25:14.425 --> 25:16.166
Okay, I know that your podcast
is important to you--

25:16.210 --> 25:17.428
- Do you?

25:17.472 --> 25:18.908
I've been working
on this for years.

25:18.952 --> 25:21.215
This is my one shot.
- Yeah, I get that.

25:21.258 --> 25:23.043
But we also need to help Katie.
- "We"?

25:23.086 --> 25:24.610
When did this become
about "we"?

25:24.653 --> 25:26.307
The only reason why you're
here is to avoid

25:26.350 --> 25:29.745
being with your mom.
- [exhales forcefully]

25:29.789 --> 25:32.139
Wow.

25:32.182 --> 25:33.314
Okay.

25:33.357 --> 25:36.317
[tense music]

25:36.360 --> 25:37.753
♪

25:37.797 --> 25:40.539
- I didn't ask for this.

25:40.582 --> 25:44.107
You wanna help Katie,
be my guest.

25:44.151 --> 25:45.326
But I'm done.

25:45.369 --> 25:47.415
♪

25:47.458 --> 25:48.808
- [exhales]

25:48.851 --> 25:50.766
♪

25:50.810 --> 25:53.160
Fine.

25:53.203 --> 25:54.857
You don't wanna help Katie,
I will.

26:04.998 --> 26:06.565
♪

26:06.608 --> 26:08.871
- God is nothing but a lie--

26:08.915 --> 26:11.482
a made-up fairy tale
to control the masses.

26:11.526 --> 26:16.052
So come take a drive through a
godless world together with me,

26:16.096 --> 26:18.141
the Millennial Prophet.

26:18.185 --> 26:21.754
- All right, Miles,
uh, let's go again.

26:21.797 --> 26:23.625
A little more energy
this time.

26:23.669 --> 26:28.108
And, uh, I guess
really--really believe

26:28.151 --> 26:29.979
what you're saying, okay?

26:30.023 --> 26:33.635
- Okay, well, is it okay
if I rework some of this

26:33.679 --> 26:36.116
to make it sound a little
bit more like me?

26:36.159 --> 26:38.074
- Yeah, don't--don't
overthink it.

26:38.118 --> 26:40.163
Just, um, trust me, okay?

26:40.207 --> 26:42.296
This is what your
listeners want to hear.

26:42.339 --> 26:43.645
- Okay.
- All right.

26:43.689 --> 26:45.212
[cell phone buzzes and chimes]

26:47.257 --> 26:50.217
[dramatic music]

26:50.260 --> 26:53.002
All right, Miles.
Let's go again.

26:53.046 --> 26:55.222
- Yeah, yeah, I'm ready.
Sorry.

26:55.265 --> 27:00.096
- I feel like a dagger has been
plunged through my heart

27:00.140 --> 27:03.143
over and over and over.
- So, wait.

27:03.186 --> 27:05.493
Did you actually speak to Jaya,

27:05.536 --> 27:07.669
or did you just
interpret what you saw?

27:07.713 --> 27:10.411
- Of course I did
not speak to her.

27:10.454 --> 27:11.717
I threw up on the side
of the street,

27:11.760 --> 27:13.370
then I came right here.
- Okay.

27:13.414 --> 27:14.676
- I guess, you know,
it's my fault.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.547
It's my fault.

27:16.591 --> 27:19.246
I somehow convinced myself that
someone as beautiful as Jaya

27:19.289 --> 27:23.250
is gonna be interested in me,
customer service rep

27:23.293 --> 27:25.034
who lives in
his parents' basement.

27:25.078 --> 27:28.211
- Yeah.
But it's a nice basement.

27:28.255 --> 27:29.865
- [chuckles]

27:29.909 --> 27:32.259
Don't try and make
me feel better.

27:32.302 --> 27:34.000
I'm just not good
at relationships.

27:34.043 --> 27:36.872
- That's just because you've
never been in a serious one.

27:36.916 --> 27:38.657
Likely a defense mechanism.

27:38.700 --> 27:42.791
And now that you found
someone you actually like,

27:42.835 --> 27:45.707
you're scared you're
gonna screw it up.

27:45.751 --> 27:47.535
- You're good.
- Oh, thank you.

27:47.578 --> 27:49.798
[both laughing]

27:49.842 --> 27:52.366
♪

27:52.409 --> 27:54.847
- God is nothing but a lie.
[echoing]

27:54.890 --> 27:57.980
[feedback screeching]

28:00.026 --> 28:01.201
- Listen, sorry about that,
Miles.

28:01.244 --> 28:02.724
It's, uh--just a minute.

28:02.768 --> 28:04.030
It's a little
technical difficulty.

28:04.073 --> 28:09.165
♪

28:09.209 --> 28:11.733
Oh, hey, uh, corporate
sent these over.

28:11.777 --> 28:13.039
A little
welcome-to-the-family gift.

28:13.082 --> 28:14.562
Good luck, right?

28:14.605 --> 28:16.738
- Uh...

28:16.782 --> 28:19.045
Y--uh, yeah, th--thanks.

28:19.088 --> 28:21.177
Uh, is--is everything
okay with the sound?

28:21.221 --> 28:24.224
- Yeah, it's, uh, just
a little technical glitch.

28:24.267 --> 28:26.313
Nothing to worry about.

28:26.356 --> 28:29.751
The engineers need
to reboot the system.

28:29.795 --> 28:32.580
Why don't you take a break,
come back in a couple hours,

28:32.623 --> 28:33.755
and we finish up then?

28:33.799 --> 28:36.062
♪

28:36.105 --> 28:37.716
- Oka--okay.
Okay.

28:37.759 --> 28:40.762
♪

28:40.806 --> 28:43.417
- Oh, well if it isn't
the man of the hour.

28:43.460 --> 28:45.985
- Rakesh, I'm pretty sure
the God account just sabotaged

28:46.028 --> 28:48.770
my promo at Frequency.
Cara said that you have a lead.

28:48.814 --> 28:50.859
- I did, Miles.
I did.

28:50.903 --> 28:53.601
But, uh, I kinda got
sidetracked and lost it,

28:53.644 --> 28:56.560
so trail's gone cold,
my friend.

28:56.604 --> 28:58.301
Just like life.

28:58.345 --> 29:01.261
- Wh...
- Don't ask.

29:01.304 --> 29:04.003
- Okay, well, is Cara here?
- No, not yet.

29:06.135 --> 29:10.487
Miles, what did you do?
- Don't ask.

29:10.531 --> 29:12.576
- Oh, crap.
I forgot I invited her.

29:12.620 --> 29:14.100
Do not let her see me, okay?

29:14.143 --> 29:15.754
- Yeah, it's a little
too late for that.

29:18.191 --> 29:21.237
- Rakesh, what's going on?

29:21.281 --> 29:24.806
- Uh, nothing.
I, uh--I--I--

29:24.850 --> 29:27.809
I wanna go over there
and sit down.

29:27.853 --> 29:30.333
- Why?
- I just do.

29:30.377 --> 29:32.031
I wanna go sit on that chair.

29:32.074 --> 29:35.338
You wanna go on lunch dates
with pretty-boy banker types.

29:35.382 --> 29:37.123
It's--it's all good.
It's all good.

29:37.166 --> 29:39.821
I--we're all free
to do whatever we want.

29:48.221 --> 29:52.486
- So you were, what,
following me?

29:52.529 --> 29:56.185
- No, I was following God.

29:56.229 --> 29:59.014
Look, that's not important.
Stop turning this around on me.

29:59.058 --> 30:01.408
- I'm not turning
anything around.

30:01.451 --> 30:03.279
Look, Rakesh,
what you saw was just--

30:03.323 --> 30:04.759
- Was none of my business.
I get that.

30:04.803 --> 30:06.848
I totally get it.
I misread the situation.

30:06.892 --> 30:10.547
I thought--I thought we
had a real connection.

30:10.591 --> 30:12.854
And clearly you've got that
connection with a lot of guys.

30:14.900 --> 30:18.947
- That's what you think of me?
- I'm just being a realist.

30:18.991 --> 30:21.820
- No, no, you're
just being an idiot.

30:25.736 --> 30:28.348
- So, what happened
with your promo?

30:28.391 --> 30:30.524
- Something.
Nothing.

30:30.567 --> 30:32.787
I don't know.
[stammers]

30:32.831 --> 30:34.615
I'm supposed to be back
in a few hours.

30:34.658 --> 30:36.443
- You don't sound excited.

30:36.486 --> 30:38.010
I thought this is
what you always wanted.

30:38.053 --> 30:40.751
- Oh, no, it is.
It's just...

30:40.795 --> 30:42.753
like, it's not what I expected.

30:42.797 --> 30:45.234
You know, it's like they're
trying to make me into

30:45.278 --> 30:47.889
something I'm not, or...

30:47.933 --> 30:51.937
maybe they're asking me
to be who I am.

30:54.113 --> 30:56.724
I'm not really sure anymore.

30:56.767 --> 30:59.858
- Maybe that's what
you have to figure out.

30:59.901 --> 31:01.207
- Yeah.

31:01.250 --> 31:03.513
Oh, and I was such
a jerk to Cara.

31:03.557 --> 31:05.037
- Oh, I knew that.

31:05.080 --> 31:06.865
I was just wondering why
you haven't called her yet.

31:09.302 --> 31:12.044
[stirring music]

31:12.087 --> 31:16.831
♪

31:16.875 --> 31:19.834
[cell phone ringing]

31:19.878 --> 31:22.924
♪

31:22.968 --> 31:24.839
- [sighs]

31:24.883 --> 31:26.797
[knocking]

31:29.539 --> 31:33.369
- Dad.
- Hello. [chuckles]

31:33.413 --> 31:34.980
[kisses]
Whoa.

31:35.023 --> 31:37.069
- I'm gonna go get you a drink.

31:37.112 --> 31:39.723
- [chuckles]
- Well, I'm surprised you came.

31:39.767 --> 31:41.377
- That makes two of us.

31:41.421 --> 31:44.511
- No, I mean, it means a lot--
you know, you being here.

31:44.554 --> 31:47.644
What changed your mind?
- Uh, what do you mean?

31:49.472 --> 31:51.518
- Nothing, nothing.

31:51.561 --> 31:54.216
Just glad you listened
to my podcast.

31:54.260 --> 31:56.610
- Look, Miles--
- You didn't listen to--

31:56.653 --> 31:59.656
- I know you're disappointed,
but I'm here to support you.

31:59.700 --> 32:01.441
- How is that, exactly?

32:01.484 --> 32:03.530
- I don't need to listen
to the show to know what it is.

32:03.573 --> 32:05.097
I mean, I've heard
this conversation before.

32:05.140 --> 32:07.099
People railing against God.

32:07.142 --> 32:09.275
And--and it is always
a one-sided conversation.

32:09.318 --> 32:10.885
- No, it is not.

32:10.929 --> 32:12.887
The--the only one-sided
conversation that we're having

32:12.931 --> 32:14.889
is this one, and you would
know that if you listened

32:14.933 --> 32:16.412
to my podcast, Dad.

32:16.456 --> 32:18.197
- Come on, Miles,
you keep talking about

32:18.240 --> 32:21.417
a one-sided conversation.
Then let's change the subject.

32:21.461 --> 32:24.638
Uh, the Yankees beat
the Sox three to two,

32:24.681 --> 32:27.989
bottom of the ninth
the other night.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.425
See now,
when you were in high school,

32:29.469 --> 32:30.905
we would have gone through
the stat lineup.

32:30.949 --> 32:32.124
- You wanna talk
about baseball.

32:32.167 --> 32:33.908
- I want to talk
about anything.

32:33.952 --> 32:36.824
- Other than the one thing
that matters the most to me.

32:36.867 --> 32:38.652
[tense music]

32:38.695 --> 32:40.654
♪

32:40.697 --> 32:42.525
Dad, if you can't do that,
then we cannot have

32:42.569 --> 32:44.092
a real relationship.

32:44.136 --> 32:46.138
♪

32:46.181 --> 32:48.140
[cell phone buzzes]

32:48.183 --> 32:51.882
♪

32:51.926 --> 32:53.232
I'm sorry.
I have to take this.

32:53.275 --> 32:56.583
♪

32:56.626 --> 32:58.933
Hey, Cara, what's up?
- Miles, listen to me.

32:58.977 --> 33:00.891
You need to get down here.
- Down where?

33:00.935 --> 33:02.719
Where--what are you
talking about?

33:02.763 --> 33:05.853
- I'm at Katie's apartment.
Her son Nate's gone missing.

33:05.896 --> 33:08.029
- Okay, stay right there.

33:08.073 --> 33:09.813
I have to go.

33:17.256 --> 33:20.172
♪

33:20.215 --> 33:21.608
- Hey.
[car door slams shut]

33:21.651 --> 33:23.305
Anything?
- No.

33:23.349 --> 33:25.046
- Thank you for calling.

33:25.090 --> 33:29.268
♪

33:29.311 --> 33:31.879
- I gave them
a picture of Nate.

33:31.922 --> 33:34.490
They're, uh--they're searching
the neighborhood now.

33:34.534 --> 33:36.492
But, uh, he's so alone.

33:36.536 --> 33:38.625
- Wait, how long
has he been gone?

33:38.668 --> 33:40.931
- Almost two hours.
- Hey, look.

33:40.975 --> 33:42.194
We're gonna find him.

33:44.935 --> 33:46.937
- This is all my fault.
- No.

33:46.981 --> 33:48.200
No, no, no, no, no, no.

33:48.243 --> 33:49.853
You cannot blame
this on yourself.

33:49.897 --> 33:51.812
- You don't understand.

33:51.855 --> 33:54.336
When we got home
from the music store, I...

33:54.380 --> 33:56.469
I was so emotional,
I--I broke down.

33:56.512 --> 33:58.949
I just started crying.

33:58.993 --> 34:01.039
It must have freaked him out.

34:01.082 --> 34:03.345
I turned around and he had--
he was gone!

34:03.389 --> 34:07.088
- Look, I--I'm really sorry
we left the restaurant, okay?

34:07.132 --> 34:08.611
[stammers] I didn't know
how to stop him.

34:08.655 --> 34:10.744
- No, it's not that.

34:10.787 --> 34:14.400
When I saw him in there...

34:14.443 --> 34:17.794
he smiled at you.

34:17.838 --> 34:19.927
He's never smiled at me.

34:19.970 --> 34:23.104
Do you have any idea
what that feels like?

34:23.148 --> 34:25.846
To not be able to connect with
the person you love most

34:25.889 --> 34:27.804
in the world?

34:27.848 --> 34:31.460
I try so hard
to reach him, but...

34:31.504 --> 34:34.463
I don't know if
he can even hear me.

34:34.507 --> 34:37.814
I've tried everything
to get through to him.

34:37.858 --> 34:40.991
But you come into his
life for a few hours.

34:41.035 --> 34:43.081
A few hours.

34:43.124 --> 34:45.866
And you're able to connect
with him in a way that...

34:45.909 --> 34:47.172
I never have.

34:47.215 --> 34:49.783
[stirring music]

34:49.826 --> 34:51.306
And probably never will.

34:51.350 --> 34:53.439
♪

34:53.482 --> 34:56.703
- It wasn't me
who he connected to.

34:56.746 --> 34:58.400
It was the music.

34:58.444 --> 35:03.840
♪

35:03.884 --> 35:07.148
I think I know where he went.

35:07.192 --> 35:09.542
Oh, no, it's closed.

35:09.585 --> 35:11.500
Hey, open up!

35:11.544 --> 35:13.154
Look, there's someone in there.

35:13.198 --> 35:14.590
[latches unlocking]

35:14.634 --> 35:16.505
- Can I help you?

35:16.549 --> 35:18.551
- Please, have you seen my son?
He's--he's eight years old.

35:18.594 --> 35:20.118
He has special needs.
He was wearing a Yankees hat.

35:20.161 --> 35:21.249
- We were just in here.

35:21.293 --> 35:22.511
I was playing
the piano for him.

35:22.555 --> 35:24.209
- Yeah, that's right.
"Lean on Me."

35:24.252 --> 35:27.255
Yeah, he showed up not long
ago, just as we were closing.

35:27.299 --> 35:28.604
- Do you have any
idea where he went?

35:28.648 --> 35:30.302
- No, sorry.
He took off.

35:30.345 --> 35:33.348
I figured he was with someone.
- Okay, okay, thank you.

35:33.392 --> 35:35.089
Thanks.
- Oh, my God.

35:35.133 --> 35:37.047
Oh, my God.
Nate?

35:37.091 --> 35:38.048
[screaming] Nate?
- Katie.

35:38.092 --> 35:39.093
- Nate!
- Katie.

35:39.137 --> 35:40.529
- [crying]
- Okay.

35:40.573 --> 35:42.662
We know that he was here
and that he was safe.

35:42.705 --> 35:44.229
Okay, we just--just
need to figure out

35:44.272 --> 35:45.795
where he's going next.
- She's right, okay?

35:45.839 --> 35:47.232
- Now--now, he came here
for a reason.

35:47.275 --> 35:48.755
Uh, the piano,
but he never got to it

35:48.798 --> 35:50.191
because the store was closing.

35:50.235 --> 35:51.627
- You think he's looking
for another piano?

35:51.671 --> 35:53.020
- Why?
- I'm not sure,

35:53.063 --> 35:54.587
but maybe that's where
he's headed to next.

35:54.630 --> 35:56.371
- Okay, well, I'll look
for the closest music store

35:56.415 --> 35:57.372
in the area.

35:57.416 --> 35:59.722
[music brightens]

35:59.766 --> 36:01.681
- Wait, wait, wait.
Don't bother.

36:01.724 --> 36:03.204
Look.

36:03.248 --> 36:05.163
♪

36:05.206 --> 36:07.382
- Central Park's not
too far from here.

36:07.426 --> 36:09.123
- Yeah, let's go.

36:10.429 --> 36:13.388
[flowing piano music]

36:13.432 --> 36:19.568
♪

36:19.612 --> 36:21.048
- Nate?

36:21.091 --> 36:27.097
♪

36:27.141 --> 36:29.274
I don't understand.

36:29.317 --> 36:31.232
♪

36:31.276 --> 36:33.539
Did--did you--did you
teach him how to play?

36:33.582 --> 36:34.844
- No.

36:34.888 --> 36:36.977
No, I just showed him
a few notes.

36:37.020 --> 36:38.239
- What song is he playing?

36:38.283 --> 36:40.676
♪

36:40.720 --> 36:43.940
- [softly] "Beautiful Boy"
by John Lennon.

36:43.984 --> 36:46.508
♪

36:46.552 --> 36:49.642
It's the song I've sung to him
every night since he was born.

36:49.685 --> 36:55.125
♪

36:55.169 --> 36:59.260
- You said he doesn't hear you.

36:59.304 --> 37:01.784
Well, I think this is his way
of telling you that he does.

37:01.828 --> 37:08.835
♪

37:30.030 --> 37:36.819
♪

37:48.048 --> 37:54.054
- ♪ Beautiful, beautiful,
beautiful, beautiful boy ♪

37:54.097 --> 37:58.667
♪

37:58.711 --> 38:01.496
[crying]

38:01.540 --> 38:08.547
♪

38:11.506 --> 38:14.030
- [exhales]

38:16.381 --> 38:18.339
It's weird.

38:18.383 --> 38:21.342
Those angel wings,
I saw them yesterday.

38:21.386 --> 38:24.127
- Maybe it was a sign.

38:24.171 --> 38:26.739
Or just a coincidence.

38:28.393 --> 38:31.526
- Look, about what
I said earlier...

38:31.570 --> 38:33.136
I'm sorry.

38:33.180 --> 38:36.966
Okay, I was frustrated
and I took it out on you.

38:37.010 --> 38:38.707
- Yeah, you were
kind of a jerk.

38:38.751 --> 38:40.622
- Yes, I was.

38:40.666 --> 38:43.582
But that didn't stop you
from helping Katie.

38:43.625 --> 38:45.497
You kept going
and because of that,

38:45.540 --> 38:47.368
she was able to find Nate.

38:47.412 --> 38:48.891
I mean,
after everything that I said,

38:48.935 --> 38:51.285
I'm really surprised
that you called me.

38:51.329 --> 38:54.070
- Well, I knew you weren't
really walking away.

38:54.114 --> 38:56.769
Or at least, I hope so.

38:56.812 --> 39:01.730
You know, you were right
about one thing.

39:01.774 --> 39:06.213
I was using the God account
as an excuse to avoid my mom.

39:06.256 --> 39:08.302
I just couldn't figure out
how to talk to her.

39:09.738 --> 39:11.784
- Maybe it's like
Katie and Nate.

39:11.827 --> 39:14.569
Just gotta find your own
version of music.

39:14.613 --> 39:17.442
[cell phone buzzes and chimes]

39:18.834 --> 39:20.401
- Is everything okay?

39:20.445 --> 39:22.229
- Yeah.

39:22.272 --> 39:25.101
Yeah, there's just something
I have to take care of.

39:25.145 --> 39:27.147
I'll talk to you later?
- Yeah.

39:31.934 --> 39:34.807
- I know you want me to be
the guy talking to one side,

39:34.850 --> 39:37.766
but I really think people are
ready to have a conversation.

39:37.810 --> 39:39.725
- You're an atheist, Miles.

39:39.768 --> 39:41.596
What kind of conversation
do you wanna have?

39:41.640 --> 39:43.598
- One where I can get
the other side to listen

39:43.642 --> 39:46.427
and change
a few people's minds.

39:46.471 --> 39:49.474
- I'm sorry.
You're wrong.

39:49.517 --> 39:51.780
I know what's best
for your show.

39:51.824 --> 39:53.391
- Maybe.

39:53.434 --> 39:55.958
But it's not what's
best for me right now.

39:56.002 --> 39:57.699
And it's crazy.

39:57.743 --> 39:59.962
A few weeks ago I would
have jumped at the chance.

40:01.355 --> 40:02.617
- What changed?

40:04.489 --> 40:06.795
- That's a good question.

40:06.839 --> 40:09.189
Guess you'll have to tune in
to my podcast to find out.

40:11.365 --> 40:12.845
Thank you.

40:12.888 --> 40:15.717
[George FitzGerald's
"Roll Back"]

40:15.761 --> 40:17.937
Humans are social creatures.

40:17.980 --> 40:21.462
Communication is the foundation
of our culture.

40:21.506 --> 40:23.769
It's supposed to be
how we all connect.

40:23.812 --> 40:27.468
But in an age where
everyone's talking,

40:27.512 --> 40:30.210
we've forgotten how
to have a conversation.

40:30.253 --> 40:32.168
- What are you doing here?

40:32.212 --> 40:35.171
- Hey, uh...

40:35.215 --> 40:36.738
I thought about what you said.

40:36.782 --> 40:38.610
And, uh, you were right.

40:38.653 --> 40:40.350
I was an idiot.

40:40.394 --> 40:42.309
- ♪ Is it cold when
you're under? ♪

40:42.352 --> 40:43.353
- No arguments here.

40:43.397 --> 40:45.617
- I totally overreacted.

40:45.660 --> 40:47.488
- ♪ Roll back to yesterday

40:47.532 --> 40:49.838
- Keep going.

40:49.882 --> 40:51.884
- Well, everything
I said is just--

40:51.927 --> 40:54.016
it's not how I feel.
[stammering] I...

40:54.060 --> 40:56.889
[sighs]
I think you're great.

40:56.932 --> 40:58.499
Um...

40:58.543 --> 41:00.719
I'm just not good at this.
[chuckles]

41:00.762 --> 41:04.200
So...I just came
to say I'm sorry.

41:04.244 --> 41:07.029
♪

41:07.073 --> 41:09.075
- So, that's it?

41:09.118 --> 41:11.077
You're just gonna give up?

41:11.120 --> 41:12.992
- What do you mean?

41:13.035 --> 41:16.909
- Look, Rakesh, we just met.
And you're fun.

41:16.952 --> 41:18.998
But if this is gonna
go somewhere,

41:19.041 --> 41:21.696
then we have to be
able to communicate.

41:21.740 --> 41:23.002
- But the--
- Yes.

41:23.045 --> 41:25.221
It was a date.

41:25.265 --> 41:29.051
But I set it up before we met,
so...

41:29.095 --> 41:31.924
- Okay, so where does
that leave us?

41:31.967 --> 41:33.926
- Depends.

41:33.969 --> 41:35.101
Can you still get
us reservations

41:35.144 --> 41:36.885
for that vegan place?

41:36.929 --> 41:38.583
- ♪ Is it cold when
you're dreaming? ♪

41:38.626 --> 41:40.715
- Maybe it's about
finding a new language...

41:40.759 --> 41:43.326
- Hey.
You mind if I join you?

41:43.370 --> 41:46.678
- ♪ Roll back to yesterday

41:46.721 --> 41:48.288
- I'd like that.

41:48.331 --> 41:50.682
[both laugh]

41:50.725 --> 41:52.466
- ♪ Is it cold when
you're under? ♪

41:52.510 --> 41:55.556
- Or putting aside
our differences...

41:55.600 --> 41:56.818
- ♪ Roll back to yesterday

41:56.862 --> 41:58.516
- And really listening.

